> Our Harissa Sweet Potato and Butter Bean Stew is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!

Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @diced sweet potato{200%g} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @Chermoula Spice Mix{½%sachet}.

Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then cut in half widthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a large #saucepan on high heat. Once hot, add the pepper and fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve. Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay it onto another baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over half the garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread.

Once the pepper has softened, reduce the heat to medium-high, then add the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @harissa paste{50%g}, remaining chermoula (use less if you'd prefer things milder) and the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{200%ml} for the sauce.

Stir in the butter beans and season with salt and pepper.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Pop the ciabatta onto the middle shelf of your #oven until toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @dill{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

When everything's ready, stir the roasted sweet potato and half the dill into the stew.

Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.

Cut the garlic ciabatta diagonally into triangles.

Share the harissa stew between your bowls.

Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g} and garnish with the remaining dill.

Serve the garlic ciabatta dippers on the side. Enjoy!